{"variants":[{"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}],"paths":["\/documentation\/gio\/taskprotocol\/runinthread(taskfunc:)"]}],"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO","doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/TaskProtocol"]]},"primaryContentSections":[{"declarations":[{"languages":["swift"],"tokens":[{"text":"func","kind":"keyword"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"text":"runInThread","kind":"identifier"},{"text":"(","kind":"text"},{"text":"taskFunc","kind":"externalParam"},{"kind":"text","text":": "},{"kind":"typeIdentifier","preciseIdentifier":"c:@T@GTaskThreadFunc","text":"GTaskThreadFunc"},{"kind":"text","text":"?)"}],"platforms":["macOS"]}],"kind":"declarations"},{"kind":"content","content":[{"type":"heading","text":"Discussion","level":2,"anchor":"discussion"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"This takes a ref on "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"task"},{"text":" until the task completes.","type":"text"}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"See "},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/TaskThreadFunc","type":"reference","isActive":true},{"text":" for more details about how ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"taskFunc"},{"text":" is handled.","type":"text"}]},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Although GLib currently rate-limits the tasks queued via"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"g_task_run_in_thread()"},{"text":", you should not assume that it will always","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"do this. If you have a very large number of tasks to run (several tens of"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"tasks), but don’t want them to all run at once, you should only queue a"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"limited number of them (around ten) at a time."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Be aware that if your task depends on other tasks to complete, use of this","type":"text"},{"text":